fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.design

Interface IPageProcessor


  • @PluginService
public interface IPageProcessor
    Provides a filtering capability for standard template-based page flow for ViewShell applications.

    Standard page flow begins:

    • after the HTTP service has directed an incoming request to the IDesignService, and
    • after authentication filters have allowed access to the requested address, and
    • after the page service has selected page processors that can process request, to intercept and possibly modify the default behavior.

    Standard page flow involves thereafter:

    • allowing modification of any submitted data (using beforeDataFilter and beforeDataStore),
    • retrieving data for display (using afterDataListFetch and afterDataItemFetch),
    • allowing modification of the displayable data and templates (using beforeFormPageMerge),
    • filtering merged template output (using filterTemplateMerge) for non-binary format templates.

    The template data context will initially be populated with the following keys:

    • mediaUri
    • themeMediaUri
    • contextUri
    • asset
    • styleSheet
    • dictionary
    • page
    • routeContext
    • user

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be immutable and must be completely thread-safe for concurrent usage. Operations are to be performed using method parameters only, without requiring any state to be maintained between method calls. Method parameters are not guaranteed to be immutable.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Detail

      • canProcess

        boolean canProcess(IPageProcessorContext context)
        Determines if a page processor will be used to filter each step of page processing. This notification is the first step in processing, and enables available processors to opt in or out of processing for a specific context.

        Depending upon the context, some filter methods may not be required and will not be invoked. For example, when accessing a list or form for the first time using standard page flow, there will be nothing to store, so beforeDataStore(IPageProcessorContext, java.util.List) will not be required.

        Parameters:
        context - the non-null page processor context, providing access to the user, the page, and a simple key-value attribute store for tracking state information.
        Returns:
        true if the process should be participate in filtering some or all of the subsequent filtering of page processing steps, otherwise false.
        Since:
        1.0

      • beforeDataFilter

        default IFilter beforeDataFilter(IPageProcessorContext context,
                                 IFilter filter)
        Optionally replaces or modifies a search filter to be applied before fetching a list.

        When this is not required, this method should return null.

        Parameters:
        context - the page processing context, including the user, the data page, and a stateful page processing attribute map.
        filter - search filter that will be applied before fetching a list, unless modified by this method. May be null, in which case this callback is an opportunity to provide a default filter. May be subsequently modified by an instance of IListFetchFilter.
        Returns:
        the modified (or unchanged) search filter, or an alternative search filter, or null if no changes are required.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IFilter.and(IFilter), IListFetchFilter.beforeDataListFetch(fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.views.IListView)

      • beforeDataStore

        default List<IItem> beforeDataStore(IPageProcessorContext context,
                                    List<IItem> items)
        Optionally replaces or modifies items or attributes about to stored.

        When this is not required, this method should return null.

        Parameters:
        context - the page processing context, including the user, the data page, and a stateful page processing attribute map.
        items - items that will be stored, unless modified by this method.
        Returns:
        the modified (or unchanged) list of items to store, or an alternative list of items to store, or null if no changes are required.
        Since:
        1.0

      • beforeDataMerge

        default void beforeDataMerge(IPageProcessorContext context,
                             ITemplateData templateData)
        Allows modification of the data to be merged into the template.
        Parameters:
        context - the page processing context, including the user, the data page, and a stateful page processing attribute map.
        templateData - the current container for data to be merged into the page template. The contents can be changed before being merged into the template file by the template engine.
        Since:

      • filterTemplateMerge

        default FilterWriter filterTemplateMerge(IPageProcessorContext context,
                                         Writer out)
        Optionally filters the output of the template merge. This is a low-level filter function, and it will not be called for binary-only template files.

        When this is not required, this method should return null.

        Parameters:
        context - the page processing context, including the user, the data page, and a stateful page processing attribute map.
        out - the output writer being used by the template engine.
        Returns:
        a filter writer that wraps the specified writer, or null to skip filtering.
        Since:
        1.0
